<bioghist altrender="history" encodinganalog="545" id="a2">
	<head>Historical Note</head>
	<p>Gov. Ella T. Grasso appointed the Governor’s Study Group on Limitation of Government Expenditures in June 1978 to study Connecticut’s fiscal situation as well as evaluate various revenue and expenditure control devices in Connecticut. Frazar B. Wilde, Chairman of the Board Emeritus, Connecticut General Life Insurance Company, chaired the 15-member group. Dr. Ronald C. Fisher served as Executive Director.</p>
</bioghist>

<scopecontent encodinganalog="520" id="a3">
<head>Scope and Content</head>
<p>Includes correspondence to Chairman Wilde, meeting minutes, preliminary and final reports, and various reference publications.</p>
</scopecontent>

